    title: "It’s now the Arduino Uno Q’s turn to get a price hike",
    summary: "Arduino's Raspberry Pi-like microcomputer the Uno Q is joining many other devices in getting a price hike this week. The 2GB version of the Uno Q, which is powered by a Qualcomm Dragonwing QRB2210 processor, will increase in price from $44 to $59, while the 4GB model is getting a slightly steeper increase from $59 [&#8230;]",
    body: "Arduino's Raspberry Pi-like microcomputer the Uno Q is joining many other devices in getting a price hike this week. The 2GB version of the Uno Q, which is powered by a Qualcomm Dragonwing QRB2210 processor, will increase in price from $44 to $59, while the 4GB model is getting a slightly steeper increase from $59 to $79. If you've been eyeing the Uno Q as a cheaper alternative to Raspberry Pi's current lineup , you have a little over a week to grab either version at the current price as the increases won't take effect until July 6th.\n\nIn a letter shared through the official Arduino blog , the company's chief product officer Marcello Majonchi …",
